The '''Star Chamber Café''' was the central reception area at the [[Lucky Despot]] Hotel & Casino in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] on the planet [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. A [[Whiphid/Legends|Whiphid]] crime lord named [[Lady/Legends|Lady]] [[Valarian/Legends|Valarian]] owned the Lucky Despot. It was here that she celebrated her wedding to the Whiphid hunter [[D'Wopp]].

Valarian hired [[Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes/Legends|Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes]] to perform at her [[Wedding of Valarian and D'Wopp|wedding]] reception. However, Valarian's underworld rival, [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]], decided to crash her party. He sent a [[Duros/Legends|Duros]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] and several other henchmen to disrupt the festivities under the pretext of protecting a prior investment. Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes were under an exclusive contract to perform only for Jabba, and the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] wanted to shut down their performance. As luck would have it, several [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] likewise raided the Star Chamber Café and engaged in a blaster fight with Jabba's cronies. Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes managed to slip out the back door of the hotel and escape into the streets of Mos Eisley.

